g.data-tooltip: Many practicing physicians stay involved with the institution that trained them. Support at IU School of Medicine can include working as faculty, volunteering, donating or otherwise participating in the Alumni Association.
Across all specialties, physicians must maintain or increase their professional knowledge and skills through seminars, training and conferences to retain a medical license.
After residency, MD graduates must apply for a state license and pass the medical board examination to practice medicine.
After completing MD training, future physicians must complete a paid residency.
Medical school is typically four years of coursework and clinical experience.
Students conduct research as a paid employee for a university. Researchers can complete more than one post-doc program.
Students interested in medical research apply for a masters or PhD program in a field of basic science.

Future physicians, medical researchers and healthcare professionals complete an undergraduate education program that prepares them for career placement as health personnel or additional training for a career in medicine.
